The paper discusses image retrieval using hashing methods based on deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of probability distributions and optimization, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for generating hash codes without weight tuning, which involves mathematical optimization and could be considered a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
